<item>
            <title>[CASSANDRA-7895] ALTER TYPE &lt;name&gt; RENAME TO &lt;name&gt; no longer parses as valid cql</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CASSANDRA-7895</link>
                <project id="12310865" key="CASSANDRA">Apache Cassandra</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Type renaming seems to be broken. The error looks like perhaps the syntax has changed or there&apos;s a problem parsing the cql.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;cqlsh:test&amp;gt; create type foo (somefield int);
cqlsh:test&amp;gt; alter type foo rename to bar;
&amp;lt;ErrorMessage code=2000 [Syntax error in CQL query] message=&quot;line 1:22 no viable alternative at input &apos;to&apos; (alter type foo rename [to] bar...)&quot;&amp;gt;
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
